# {{.ProjectName}}

Swift + SwiftUI targeting iOS {{.MinIOSVersion}}+. Bundle ID: `{{.BundleID}}`.

## Architecture (MVVM)

```
{{.ProjectName}}/
├── Views/          # SwiftUI views — pure UI, no business logic
├── ViewModels/     # @Observable classes — state, logic, data transformation
├── Models/         # Domain types, DTOs, Codable structs
├── Services/       # Network layer, persistence, external integrations
└── Navigation/     # NavigationPath-based centralized routing
```

- **Views** are functions of state — they read from ViewModels, never mutate data directly
- **ViewModels** own the state and business logic. One ViewModel per feature screen.
- **Services** are protocol-defined and injected into ViewModels — never instantiated inside VMs
- **Navigation** is centralized via `NavigationPath` with a typed route enum

